---
const COMPANY = {
  name: "DM Management Group",
  website: "https://dmmanagement.uk",
  email: "hello@dmmanagementgroup.com",
};
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Privacy Policy — {COMPANY.name}</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for DM Management Group and its applications, products, and services." />

    <style>
      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;
        background: #0b0d12;
        color: #ffffff;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 48px 24px;
      }
      h1, h2 {
        margin-top: 40px;
      }
      p, li {
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
      a {
        color: #3b82f6;
      }
      footer {
        margin-top: 64px;
        border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        padding-top: 24px;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how {COMPANY.name} ("we", "us", or "our")
        collects, uses, discloses, and processes information across our websites,
        applications, software products, platforms, and services (collectively,
        the “Services”).
      </p>

      <p>
        This policy applies to all current and future products, applications, and
        services developed, operated, or maintained by {COMPANY.name}, whether
        accessed via web, mobile application, desktop software, APIs, or other
        technologies.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We may collect information that you voluntarily provide, information
        automatically collected through your use of our Services, and
        information obtained from third parties, as permitted by law.
      </p>

      <p>Information we collect may include, but is not limited to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Names, email addresses, phone numbers, and contact details</li>
        <li>Account information and user-generated content</li>
        <li>Device, browser, operating system, and usage data</li>
        <li>Log data, analytics data, and diagnostic information</li>
        <li>Communications and support inquiries</li>
        <li>Any other information you choose to provide</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>
        We may use information collected for any lawful business purpose,
        including but not limited to:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Providing, operating, maintaining, and improving our Services</li>
        <li>Developing new products, features, and functionality</li>
        <li>Analytics, research, testing, and performance monitoring</li>
        <li>Security, fraud prevention, and abuse detection</li>
        <li>Customer support, communications, and service-related notices</li>
        <li>Compliance with legal obligations and enforcement of our rights</li>
        <li>Business operations, internal reporting, and administrative purposes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Legal Bases for Processing</h2>
      <p>
        Where required by applicable law, we process personal information based
        on one or more of the following legal grounds: consent, performance of a
        contract, compliance with legal obligations, and our legitimate business
        interests.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>
        We may use cookies, pixels, SDKs, analytics tools, and similar
        technologies to operate our Services, understand usage patterns, improve
        performance, and support lawful business activities.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        We may share information with service providers, partners, contractors,
        and vendors who assist us in operating our Services, provided such
        parties are authorized to process information on our behalf or as
        permitted by law.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain information for as long as reasonably necessary to fulfill the
        purposes described in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention
        period is required or permitted by law.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational
        safeguards to protect information. However, no system can be guaranteed
        to be 100% secure.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your location and applicable law, you may have rights to
        access, correct, delete, or object to certain processing of your personal
        information. Requests may be submitted to
        <a href={`mailto:${COMPANY.email}`}>{COMPANY.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Children’s Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our Services are not directed to children under the age required by
        applicable law, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from
        children without appropriate consent.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy at any time. Changes will be effective
        upon posting the updated policy on this page.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices,
        contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${COMPANY.email}`}>{COMPANY.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <footer>
        © {new Date().getFullYear()} {COMPANY.name}. All rights reserved.
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>

